H0.text: What is the name of the London Underground station in EastEnders. Albert Station

H1.text: What is the name of the London Underground station in EastEnders. Bridge Street Station

H2.text: What is the name of the London Underground station in EastEnders. East End Station

H3.text: What is the name of the London Underground station in EastEnders. Walford

A4.text: Walford East is a fictional London Underground station for Walford

A5.text: Walford East is located on the EastEnders tube map in the position normally occupied by the real Bromley-by-Bow tube station

A6.text: Walford East tube station is on George Street, which first appeared on screen in late 1985 when Lou Beale (Anna Wing) collapses outside it
